review_blob: Tasty with a strong bitter finish and nice balanced colours and flavours. Clear and crisp
Clear and crisp though nothing special but well brewed and a good straightforward pint
Plain and easy drinking maybe as I am drinking accompanied by spicy food but could be a good quaffing ale
Felt like it was going to be more than it was but good and crisp nature grows on you. Better if cooler methinks or if it was sunnier here!
Quite rich cooked palate with breadth in taste and flavour that fills the mouth too - now just need to win the 5000 they are giving away!!
